Four suspected kidnappers were yesterday arrested by the surveillance squad of the FCT, Kwali Police command, Abuja after a gun battle. It was gathered that the kidnappers, who shot sporadically had abducted seven people traveling through Lokoja express way before they were arrested. The suspects who were between the age bracket of 18 to 20 years were arrested between Yangoji,  Piri along Kwali Lokoja road yesterday evening in Abuja. The culprits were apprehended through the efforts of Gumbo community in Kwali Area Council. In a statement issued to newsmen by the Chief Press Secretary to the chairman of Kwali area council, Alhaji Isa Iya Pai said that the council chairman, Hon Danladi Chiya has vowed to see the end of kidnapping in the area. Chiya also advised ward heads and community leaders to report any suspected character to the law enforcement agents for necessary action. The four kidnappers were handed over to FCT Police command.